description:
ESPN "30 for 30" sports documentary shorts -- Cutthroat


Clint Malarchuk was "the Cowboy Goalie," infamous for surviving one of the most gruesome injuries in the history of sports.  Cutthroat details his remarkable physical, emotional and mental recovery; including treatment for obsessive-compulsive disorder (OCD) and post-traumatic stress disorder (PTSD).
